article.description: Junior guard Monica Wright had 23 points and 13 rebounds to lift Virginia (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) past East Carolina 80-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Wright scores 23, grabs 13 rebounds as Virginia cruises
article.story:
CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. -- Junior guard Monica Wright had 23 points and 13 rebounds to lift Virginia (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) past East Carolina 80-67 on Saturday.

Wright, who has led the Cavaliers (7-2) in scoring the past four games, was 9-of-20 from the field. Center Aisha Mohammed added 20 points and nine rebounds for Virginia, while Ariana Moorer had 19 points.

LaCoya Terry paced the Pirates (4-3) with 25 points. The senior guard scored 17 points in the opening half, but Virginia used a 16-6 run entering halftime to take a 45-36 lead.

The Cavaliers, who shot 43.5 percent from the field (30-of-69), pulled away in the second half, taking a 77-58 lead with 4:58 left on a floater by Britnee Millner.

East Carolina, which committed 25 turnovers, shot 35.2 percent from the field (25-of-71).
